17/11/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Wrapping up talks in Brussels on Tuesday (16 November), finance ministers of the EU member states asked Greece to control its public deficit, which was recently shown to have exceeded the Eurozone limit -- 3 per cent of GDP -- for years. The EU finance chiefs also stressed the importance of Greece's full compliance with rules related to the single currency. Greek Finance Minister Giorgos Alogoskoufis expressed satisfaction with his counterparts' position. (ANA - 17/11/04; AFP, MPA - 16/11/04)
